+## capture playwright
+
+Captures a browser-rendered page with Playwright when the optional Playwright dependency is installed. If Playwright is not installed, the command exits with an install hint and does not affect the rest of the CLI.
+
+Install:
+
+```text
+python -m pip install playwright
+python -m playwright install chromium
+```
+
+Capture page text:
+
+```text
+python pala.py capture playwright --url http://127.0.0.1:8765
+```
+
+Capture page text and screenshot:
+
+```text
+python pala.py capture playwright --url http://127.0.0.1:8765 --screenshot --full-page
+```
+
+Authenticated pages can use a Playwright storage state file. Pala Memory Core does not create or steal browser sessions by itself; the user supplies the state file:
+
+```text
+python pala.py capture playwright --url https://chatgpt.com --storage-state auth-state.json --screenshot
+```
+
+Useful options:
+
+| Option | Purpose |
+|---|---|
+| `--browser chromium` | Choose `chromium`, `firefox`, or `webkit` |
+| `--headed` | Show browser window |
+| `--screenshot` | Save screenshot as attachment |
+| `--full-page` | Full-page screenshot |
+| `--storage-state auth-state.json` | Use saved authenticated session state |
+| `--wait-until networkidle` | Page load strategy |
+| `--wait-ms 1000` | Extra wait after load |
+
