+## Playwright Capture Behavior
+
+The Playwright connector is optional. It captures browser-rendered page text and can attach screenshots.
+
+| Mode | Behavior |
+|---|---|
+| `capture playwright --url ...` | Captures rendered page text |
+| `--screenshot` | Saves screenshot as attachment |
+| `--storage-state <json>` | Uses a Playwright authenticated session state |
+
+If Playwright is missing, the CLI prints the install command instead of failing silently.
+
 ## Drive Backup Behavior
 
 The first Drive connector writes a redacted package into a local folder. If that folder is inside Google Drive's desktop sync area, Google Drive handles upload.
