+# v0.10 Playwright Capture
+
+Date: 2026-06-09
+Phase: Playwright capture preview
+Status: PARTIAL overall, PASS for optional dependency guard
+
+## Goal
+
+Capture browser-rendered page text and optional screenshots into Pala Memory Core records when the optional Playwright dependency is installed.
+
+## Added Behavior
+
+| Area | Change |
+|---|---|
+| CLI | Added `python pala.py capture playwright --url <url>` |
+| Optional dependency | Uses Playwright only when installed |
+| Text capture | Captures rendered `body` text |
+| Screenshot | `--screenshot` stores PNG as attachment |
+| Auth state | `--storage-state` supports authenticated sessions |
+| Browsers | Supports `chromium`, `firefox`, `webkit` |
+
+## Install
+
+```powershell
+python -m pip install playwright
+python -m playwright install chromium
+```
+
+## Command
+
+```powershell
+python .\pala.py capture playwright --url http://127.0.0.1:8765 --screenshot --full-page
+```
+
+## Expected Result
+
+```text
+saved <record-id>
+data\records\<date>\<record-id>.md
+captured playwright url <url> screenshots=<n>
+```
+
+## Smoke Test
+
+The current environment did not have Playwright installed. The command was expected to fail with a clear install message instead of failing silently:
+
+```powershell
+python -m py_compile .\pala.py
+python .\pala.py capture --help
+python .\pala.py capture playwright --url http://127.0.0.1:8765 --screenshot
+python .\pala.py brief today
+python .\pala.py dashboard export
+```
+
+Observed output:
+
+```text
+py_compile passed
+capture help listed {browser,playwright}
+exit=1
+Playwright is not installed. Install with: python -m pip install playwright && python -m playwright install chromium
+brief saved data\reports\2026-06-09-brief.md
+dashboard data saved dashboard\records.json
+```
+
+## Release Posture
+
+This is an optional connector preview. The CLI has a dependency guard when Playwright is not installed. Authenticated ChatGPT capture requires user-provided session state and is not automatic.
